<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>{{ title or metadata.title }}</title>
  <meta name="description" content="{{ description or metadata.description }}">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Atkinson+Hyperlegible:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400;1,700&display=swap"
    rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ '/css/index.css' | url }}">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/img/favicon.png">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ '/css/prism-base16-monokai.dark.css' | url }}">
  <link rel="alternate" href="{{ metadata.feed.path | url }}" type="application/atom+xml" title="{{ metadata.title }}">
  <link rel="alternate" href="{{ metadata.jsonfeed.path | url }}" type="application/json" title="{{ metadata.title }}">
</head>
<body>

<div class="welcome">
  <header>
    <div class="header-contents">
      <div class="home"><a href="{{ '/' | url }}">{{ metadata.title }}</a></div>

      {#- Read more about `eleventy-navigation` at https://www.11ty.dev/docs/plugins/navigation/ #}
      <ul class="nav" style="display: flex; justify-content: center; flex-direction: column">
        <div>
          {%- for entry in collections.all | eleventyNavigation %}
            <li class="nav-item{% if entry.url == page.url %} nav-item-active{% endif %}"><a
                href="{{ entry.url | url }}">{{ entry.title }}</a></li>
          {%- endfor %}
        </div>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div style="text-align: center; max-width: 850px; margin: 0 auto 0 auto;">
    <h1 class="fade-in1" style="margin-top: 5rem; font-size: 50px; padding: 0 10px 0 10px;">The spatial database for
      building real-time multiplayer games</h1>
    <div class="fade-in2" style="display: flex; justify-content: space-around; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <div style="margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 25px; text-align: left; max-width: 400px; min-width: 400px;"><b>Delight
          your players.</b> Deliver scalable, persistent, 3D worlds in a fraction of the time.
      </div>
      <div style="padding-top: 25px;">
        <a href="#" class="button">
          Join our community
        </a>
        <a href="#" class="button">
          Get in touch
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="case-study-box" class="fade-in4 case-study-box">
    <a href="#"><b>New case study</b>: Learn how WorldQL helps Minecraft autoscale to thousands of players and
      reduce lag by 99%.</a>
  </div>

  <div style="text-align: center; padding: 20px; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto 0 auto;" class="fade-in3">
    <img src="/img/term.png" style="max-width: 100%;">
    <div style="height: 50px;"></div>
  </div>

</div>

<div class="page-section">
  <h1>Easy to learn yet powerful enough to build anything</h1>
  <p class="landing-para">Iterate on your multiplayer services with blistering speed: Update scripts without reloading.
    Save and restore
    world state snapshots. Don't write your own </p>
</div>

<div class="page-section">
  <h1>Ultra-modern, wicked fast</h1>
  <p class="landing-para">WorldQL's core is written in C++20 and uses Google Flatbuffers for data serialization. WorldQL
    can parse up to one
    million incoming messages per second on a mid-range CPU<sup class="citation"><a
        href="https://google.github.io/flatbuffers/flatbuffers_benchmarks.html" target="_blank">1</a></sup>.</p>
</div>
<div class="page-section">
  <h1>Build experiences on every platform</h1>
  <p>WorldQL can make queries </p>
</div>


<main{% if templateClass %} class="{{ templateClass }}"{% endif %}>
  {{ content | safe }}
</main>

<footer></footer>

<!-- Current page: {{ page.url | url }} -->
</body>
</html>
